{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id7931e251-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1432"},"text":"§ 1432.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"As used in this chapter, the term—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e252-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “draft management plan” means the plan described in section 1434(a)(1)(C)(v) ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002642"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002642"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e253-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “Magnuson-Stevens Act” means the Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1801"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.);"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e254-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “marine environment” means those areas of coastal and ocean waters, the Great Lakes and their connecting waters, and submerged lands over which the United States exercises jurisdiction, including the exclusive economic zone, consistent with international law;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e255-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “Secretary” means the Secretary of Commerce;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e256-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “State” means each of the several States, the District of Columbia, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands, American Samoa, the Virgin Islands, Guam, and any other commonwealth, territory, or possession of the United States;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e257-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"6"},"text":"(6)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" “damages” includes—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e258-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" compensation for—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id7931e259-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/A/i"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"i"},"text":"(i)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"id7931e25a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/A/i/I"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"I"},"text":"(I)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the cost of replacing, restoring, or acquiring the equivalent of a sanctuary resource; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subclause","attrib":{"id":"id7931e25b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/A/i/II"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"II"},"text":"(II)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the value of the lost use of a sanctuary resource pending its restoration or replacement or the acquisition of an equivalent sanctuary resource; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"clause","attrib":{"id":"id7931e25c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/A/ii"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"ii"},"text":"(ii)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the value of a sanctuary resource if the sanctuary resource cannot be restored or replaced or if the equivalent of such resource cannot be acquired;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e25d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the cost of damage assessments under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1443/b/2"},"text":"section 1443(b)(2) of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e25e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/C"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"C"},"text":"(C)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the reasonable cost of monitoring appropriate to the injured, restored, or replaced resources;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e25f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/D"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"D"},"text":"(D)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the cost of curation and conservation of archeological, historical, and cultural sanctuary resources; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e260-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/6/E"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"E"},"text":"(E)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the cost of enforcement actions undertaken by the Secretary in response to the destruction or loss of, or injury to, a sanctuary resource;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e261-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/7"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"7"},"text":"(7)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “response costs” means the costs of actions taken or authorized by the Secretary to minimize destruction or loss of, or injury to, sanctuary resources, or to minimize the imminent risks of such destruction, loss, or injury, including costs related to seizure, forfeiture, storage, or disposal arising from liability under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1443"},"text":"section 1443 of this title","children":[],"tail":";"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e262-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/8"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8"},"text":"(8)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “sanctuary resource” means any living or nonliving resource of a national marine sanctuary that contributes to the conservation, recreational, ecological, historical, educational, cultural, archeological, scientific, or aesthetic value of the sanctuary; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e263-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"(9)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “exclusive economic zone” means the exclusive economic zone as defined in the Magnuson-Stevens Act; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id7931e264-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1432/10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"(10)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" “System” means the National Marine Sanctuary System established by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1431"},"text":"section 1431 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id7931e265-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/532/tIII/s302"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–532, title III, § 302","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1972-10-23"},"text":"Oct. 23, 1972","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/86/1061"},"text":"86 Stat. 1061","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/332/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–332, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-08-29"},"text":"Aug. 29, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1057"},"text":"94 Stat. 1057","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/375/tII/s202/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–375, title II, § 202(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-12-21"},"text":"Dec. 21, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1822"},"text":"96 Stat. 1822","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/498/tI/s102"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–498, title I, § 102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-19"},"text":"Oct. 19, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/2297"},"text":"98 Stat. 2297","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/627/tII/s204/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–627, title II, § 204(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-07"},"text":"Nov. 7, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/3217"},"text":"102 Stat. 3217","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/tII/s2102"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, title II, § 2102","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-11-04"},"text":"Nov. 4, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/5040"},"text":"106 Stat. 5040","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/283/s9/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–283, § 9(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3367"},"text":"110 Stat. 3367","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513","children":[],"tail":", §§ 4, 19(b)(1), (2), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-13"},"text":"Nov. 13, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2382"},"text":"114 Stat. 2382","children":[],"tail":", 2392, 2393.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id7931e266-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id7931e267-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id7931e268-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1434/a/1/C"},"text":"Section 1434(a)(1)(C) of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in par. (1), was amended generally by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513/s6/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513, § 6(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-13"},"text":"Nov. 13, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2383"},"text":"114 Stat. 2383","children":[],"tail":", and, as so amended, no longer contains a cl. (v)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act, referred to in par. (2), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/265"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–265","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-04-13"},"text":"Apr. 13, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/331"},"text":"90 Stat. 331","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 38 (§ 1801 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1801"},"text":"section 1801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id7931e269-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Par. (2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513/s19/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513, § 19(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended par. (2) generally. Prior to amendment, par. (2) read as follows: “ ‘Magnuson Act’ means the Magnuson Fishery Conservation and Management Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1801"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.);”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (6)(D), (E). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", added subpars. (D) and (E)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513/s4/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513, § 4(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “, including costs related to seizure, forfeiture, storage, or disposal arising from liability under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1443"},"text":"section 1443 of this title","children":[],"tail":"” after “loss, or injury”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513/s4/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513, § 4(c)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “educational, cultural, archeological, scientific,” for “research, educational,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (9). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513/s19/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513, § 19(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Magnuson-Stevens Act” for “Magnuson Fishery Conservation and Management Act”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (10). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/513/s4/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–513, § 4(d)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (10)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Par. (6)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/283/s9/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–283, § 9(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", which directed substitution of a semicolon for “, and” at end, was executed by substituting a semicolon for the comma at end to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/283/s9/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–283, § 9(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “and” after “injury;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/s2102/e/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, § 2102(e)(1)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “1434(a)(1)(C)(v)” for “1434(a)(1)(E)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/s2102/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, § 2102(a)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “including the exclusive economic zone,” after “jurisdiction,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/s2102/e/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, § 2102(e)(2)","children":[],"tail":", struck out “and” at end."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (6)(C). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/s2102/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, § 2102(b)","children":[],"tail":", added subpar. (C)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (7). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/s2102/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, § 2102(c)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or authorized” after “taken”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (9). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/587/s2102/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–587, § 2102(d)","children":[],"tail":", added par. (9)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1988—Pars. (6) to (8). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/627"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–627","children":[],"tail":" added pars. (6) to (8)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/498"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–498","children":[],"tail":" amended section generally, substituting provisions which set forth definitions for provisions which related to the designation of sanctuaries. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1433"},"text":"section 1433 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/375"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–375","children":[],"tail":" substituted provision that Secretary submit a biennial report on or before March 1 of every other year beginning in 1984 for provision that Secretary submit an annual report on or before November 1 of each year, and substituted reference to previous two fiscal years for reference to previous fiscal year."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1980—Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/332/s2/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–332, § 2(1)","children":[],"tail":", designated existing provisions as par. (1), struck out provision that a designation under this section would become effective sixty days after it was published unless the Governor of any State involved, before the expiration of the sixty-day period, certified to Secretary that the designation, or a specified portion thereof, was unacceptable to his State, in which case the designated sanctuary would not include the area certified as unacceptable until such time as the Governor withdrew his certification of unacceptability, and added par. (2)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/332/s2/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–332, § 2(2)","children":[],"tail":", designated existing provisions as par. (2), added pars. (1), (3), and (4), and, in par. (2) as so designated, substituted “The Secretary, after consultation with other interested Federal and State agencies, shall issue necessary and reasonable regulations to implement the terms of the designation and control the activities described in it, except that all permits, licenses, and other authorizations issued pursuant to any other authority shall be valid unless such regulations otherwise provide” for “After a marine sanctuary has been designated under this section, the Secretary, after consultation with other interested Federal agencies, shall issue necessary and reasonable regulations to control any activities permitted within the designated marine sanctuary, and no permit, license, or other authorization issued pursuant to any other authority shall be valid unless the Secretary shall certify that the permitted activity is consistent with the purposes of this chapter and can be carried out within the regulations promulgated under this section”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (h). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/332/s2/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–332, § 2(3)","children":[],"tail":", added subsec. (h)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id7931e26a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id7931e26b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Regulations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/627/tII/s210"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–627, title II, § 210","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-11-07"},"text":"Nov. 7, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/102/3223"},"text":"102 Stat. 3223","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/100/627/tII/s210"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"inline","attrib":{},"text":"“Not later than one year after the date of the enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","at